    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small structures, typically large enough for a single person to comfortably enter and furnished with a payphone for public use. They are typically characterized by having a door for privacy and windows to alert others that the booth is in use.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046986/Webster's Third New International Dictionary (1986)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>裝置有投幣式公用電話的小型結構物，大小通常足夠容納一人自在地進入。其特徵為多半有門，以維護個人隱私，並有窗，可讓他人看到電話亭是否已在使用中。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Estruturas pequenas, geralmente grandes o suficiente para uma única pessoa entrar confortavelmente e equipadas com um telefone público para uso público. Eles são tipicamente caracterizados por terem uma porta para privacidade e janelas para alertar os outros que o estande está em uso.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109633/CVAA-BR Consortium (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kleinerer Bau, in der Regel groß genug, so dass eine einzelne Person sie betreten kann, ausgestattet mit einem Münztelefon für allgemeine Nutzung. Er verfügt üblicherweise über eine Tür, um die Privatsphäre zu sichern, und Fenster, die andere darauf aufmerksam machen, dass die Zelle gerade genutzt wird.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
